<number box="[1179,1208,284,310]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="10.0">10</number>
with one pair large setae. Two ovoid, subequal­sized, partially collapsed spermatheca with short, narrow necks (
<figureCitation box="[437,508,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[300,1286,563,1738]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[298,1288,556,1747]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Brachypogon (Isohelea) borkenti, n. sp. 1 – 5. female; 6. male. 1. flagellum; 2. maxillary palpus; 3. wing; 4. sternite 9; 5. spermathecae; 6. genitalia. Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157313/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[492,508,364,390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="5.0">5</number>
